Originally made her debut as an NPC girl who was accidentally dragged into USO Popularity Poll Event on 1st April 2017 and was voted in the 1st place in said poll. title: izanami_hifumi
body:
[i][[Hypnosis Mic]][/i] character. Raps under the name "GIGOLO".

Due to trauma concerning an abusive mother, Hifumi grew to be gynophobic. He tries to cure it by working as a [[host]] in Shinjuku and inventing a flashy persona, but he often reverts to his old personality when not in work mode. Making maters worse is the fact that the women from his workplace that obsess over him the most are usually mentally unstable.  

Hifumi often wears his grey [[suit]] in public, along with a [[black shirt]] and assorted [[necklace|necklaces]] and chains. He has [[blonde hair]] with green highlights.

title: kebaya
body:
A traditional blouse-dress combination that originated from the court of the Javanese Majapahit Kingdom, and is traditionally worn by women in Indonesia, Malaysia, Singapore, Brunei, southern Thailand, Cambodia and the southern part of the Philippines.

The kebaya is the [[indonesian clothes|national costume of Indonesia]], although it is more accurately endemic to the Javanese, Sundanese and Balinese peoples.

body:

The Fennec fox ([i]Vulpes zerda[/i]) is a species of true fox native to the Sahara desert, known for being the smallest canid as well for their very large ears (the largest amongst all foxes proportional to their body size).

Fennec (the Friend) wears a pink sweater over a white shirt and a white skirt. She wears elbow gloves and thighhighs with fur bracelets and anklets, all roughly colored like the actual animal's limbs. She has short blonde hair patterned like a fennec's face with black strands representing whiskers. Of course, she also has the oversized ears and the black-tipped tail of a fennec.

title: margay_(kemono_friends)
body:
A [i][[Kemono Friends]][/i] character. She is one of many "Friends" in Japari Park.

The margay ([i]Leopardus wiedii[/i]) is a species of small cat closely related to the [[ocelot_(kemono_friends)|ocelot]], native to Central and South America and known for their particularly great aptitude at tree climbing. It has also been discovered to imitate the cry of it's prey.

Margay (the Friend) is dressed with the common base outfit of the small cats (shared with [[serval_(kemono_friends)|Serval]] among others) with elements like her skirt, gloves and thighhighs being best described as "[[margay_print|margay printed]]", beige with brown spots with parts having ocelot-like marbling.
She has short hair with the same color as her outfit (margay colored?) as well as green eyes. She is one of a few Friends wearing glasses.

In the anime, she is best described as [i]the[/i] Number One fan of [[penguins_performance_project_(kemono_friends)|PPP]]. [spoiler]In the end of the episode featuring the group, she became their manager.[/spoiler]

title: irem
body:
[b]Irem[/b] (アイレム [i]Airemu[/i]) is a Japanese video game console developer and publisher, and formerly a developer and manufacturer of arcade games as well during the 80s and 90s. The company has its headquarters in Hakusan, Ishikawa Prefecture.

The company is probably best known for [[Moon Patrol]] (1982), the famous and very popular scrolling shooter [[R-Type]] (1987) and the earliest beat 'em up, [[Spartan X]] (known in the west as Kung-Fu Master). They have been a popular developer in Japan with games like Photoboy for the PC Engine and In the Hunt for the arcades, Sega Saturn, PlayStation, and PC. Irem is also known for making their arcade games extremely difficult, and most of them feature a dip switch that allows you to play a "no death mode" as a result, in order to allow gamers to be able to complete their tough games.

In 1994 during a period of video game development hiatus in the company a group of employees, tired of the company's inactivity, left Irem to form their own company under the name Nazca Corporation, which became best known for developing [[SNK]]'s [[Metal Slug]] franchise.

As a result of the 2011 Tōhoku earthquake and tsunami, Irem canceled the majority of its remaining video game projects, including Zettai Zetsumei Toshi 4: Summer Memories and Poncotsu Roman Daikatsugeki Bumpy Trot 2. Irem re-focused to become primarily a slot-machine and pachinko developer, the industry it was in before turning to video games. 

Its video game division was dissolved in April 2011 and many Irem designers, including producer Kazuma Kujo, gathered to form a new company called Granzella to continue creating games.

title: hachisuka_kotetsu
body:
Personification of the Hachisuka Kotetsu sword. Uchigatana class. Historically, the sword was the treasure of the Hachisuka Clan.

In [i][[Touken Ranbu]][/i], Hachisuka has a strong aversion to the "counterfeit" Kotetsu swords, including [[Nagasone Kotetsu]]. He takes pride in the fact that he and his self proclaimed brother [[Urashima Kotetsu]] are the real deal. In addition to this he's also a bit of a narcissist, seen in his fieldwork quote. Despite all of these negative qualities, he still secretly has respect for Nagasone, but doesn't want to admit it.

He's one of the five swords the player can choose when starting the game, alongside [[Kashuu Kiyomitsu]], [[Yamanbagiri Kunihiro]], [[Mutsu-no-Kami Yoshiyuki]], and [[Kasen Kanesada]].

He has long [[purple hair]] and [[blue eyes]], with [[white gloves]], a [[full armor|full]] [[gold armor|golden]] [[armor]] set, and golden [[armored boots]]. In his casual mode he has a [[high ponytail]] coupled with a golden [[kimono]] and [[haori]] with golden [[sandals]]. The over saturation of gold on his person references the fact that the ornate mountings of the original sword (in addition to the inscription on the sword) are colored gold. Because of this, fans see more than a [[look-alike|passing resemblance]] to him and [[Aries Muu]].

Seiyuu is Kazuyuki Okitsu. Character designer is [[Arai Teruko]].

title: tengai_makyou
body:
Literally 'Devil's World Far from Heaven' (or possibly just 'Magic World Outside of Heaven'), is an RPG series very popular in Japan and Taiwan but virtually unknown in other regions. Tengai Makyou spans four official games and various side games, all of them parodying Japan in the fictional land 'Jipang'. The games usually humorize Western society's misconceptions about Japan, however [i]The Apocalypse IV[/i] instead parodies Japanese misconceptions about America, and [i]Oriental Blue[/i] is not really humor based.

Often known as Far East of Eden, however this is technically a sub-series within Tengai Makyou, as well as the name of a in-universe source material that the series is based on. However, the cancelled releases of Tengai Makyou all used [i]Far East of Eden[/i] as the planned localized name. Only one game, [i]Kabuki Klash[/i] (Shin Den), was released in English.

The series has similarities with [[Sakura Taisen]] as both have the same creator, and Red Entertainment has worked on both series.

title: a-1_skyraider
body:
The Douglas A-1 Skyraider was an American single-seat attack aircraft. It was originally designed during World War II to replace earlier dive bombers such as the [[SB2C Helldiver]] and torpedo bombers such as the TBF Avenger.

A piston-powered, propeller-driven aircraft during the late-40s where designers were focusing on jet aircraft, it had much longer endurance than the jet fighters of its era. 

Though it entered too late to serve in World War II, it first entered combat during the Korean War. Subsequently, its advantage of long endurance allowed it to serve close air support during the Vietnam War.

It was known for "dropping a toilet":http://www.midwaysailor.com/midwayva25bomb/ in October 1965 to highlight the six millionth pound of ordnance dropped.

The aircraft was designed by Ed Heinemann who earlier designed the [[SBD Dauntless]]. He would subsequently design the [[A-4 Skyhawk]].

Kaolla Su is an eighth grade foreign exchange student who boards at the Hinata House. She goes to the same school as Shinobu Maehara. 

Liking to keep her origins a secret, it was initially thought that she was from India, or possibly even Australia. However, it was later revealed that she was actually a royal princess from the Kingdom of Molmol, an island nation in the Pacific.

A major character from [[Sayonara Zetsubou Sensei]]. 

Abiru's name literally translates to "拳[を]浴びる" - "kobushi (wo) abiru" ("to bathe in fists") - referring to her frequent injuries and bandages around her body. Often thought to be a victim of domestic violence, when in reality her injuries are caused by irate animals whose tails she loves to pull. Also possesses [[heterochromia]] eyes, although her green left eye (the other is red) is often covered by an eyepatch.

title: protagonist_(ensemble_girls!)
body:
The player character of [i][[Ensemble Girls!]][/i].
A Second year high school student who transfers to the previously all-girls Kimisaki Academy. The younger brother of "Angie", a previous Kimisaki Academy student who led a failed rebellion against the antagonists of the series. He's a plain, yet kind guy who cares about everyone equally, but likes to tease his childhood friend [[minami natsumi|Natsumi Minami]], who has a crush on him. He doesn't like to talk about his sister, as he resents her for being stuck in her shadow.

[spoiler][i][[Ensemble Stars!]][/i] reveals that the Protagonist's older sister is actually [[anzu (ensemble stars!)|Anzu]].[/spoiler]

title: azuki_nagamitsu_(touken_ranbu)
body:
[i][[Touken Ranbu]][/i] character.

A personification of an Osafune school tachi crafted by Bizen Osafune Nagamitsu. It is rumored to be the cherished sword of Uesugi Kenshin. While there are many rumors of how the blade's name came to be, one story states that an azuki bean simply fell on the sword and cleaved it in two.

Due to the "azuki" in his name, Azuki Nagamitsu is portrayed as a man who has sweetness embedded in his very core. He is a kind, fatherly man who puts the wellbeing of the childlike tantous before his own. He is also skilled at making sweets; for this reason, fans like to have the sweets-loving [[Houchou Toushirou]] approach him for food due to his parental aura.

Voiced by Kawahara Yoshihisa. Artist is [[Homerun Ken]].

title: crazy_hand
body:

His role in the universe is even less clear than Master Hand's, though it is stated that he is the destructive spirit to Master Hand's creative spirit.

He also runs a side joint called Crazy Orders, where he bargains participants with rewards for increasing challenges and a final confrontation with him.

He is often seen with his left-handed counterpart, [[Crazy Hand]].

title: alex_kidd
body:
[i][b]Alex Kidd in Miracle World[/b][/i] (アレックスキッドのミラクルワールド [i]Arekkusu Kiddo no Mirakuru Wārudo[/i]) is a 2D platform [[video game]] for the 8-bit [[Sega Master System]] [[video game]] [[game_console|console]]. It was first released in Japan on Saturday, November 1, 1986, and then was distributed to Europe, Australia and the United States in 1987. 

The game was designed by Hayashida Kotaru.

It was arguably the most widely known game in the Alex Kidd series by [[SEGA]] Corporation, due to it being built internally into most Master System II consoles as an included bundled title. It is also the very first game in the Alex Kidd series created for this character, and the most popular of all Alex Kidd games.

The [b]"Navy Cross":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Navy_Cross][/b] is the highest award for valor in combat that can be bestowed by the United States Department of the Navy, and so is typically held by members of the U.S. Navy, U.S. Marine Corps, or U.S. Coast Guard (while operating under the Department of the Navy, as for instance during World War II).

title: gargantia_contest
body:
Official contest hosted by Pixiv for [[Suisei no Gargantia]], where participants submit original character designs (entries are tagged ガルガンティア乗組員 ).  Winning designs appeared in the final episode of the anime series.

The contest ran from Friday, April 26th 2013 to Sunday, May 12th 2013.

"The theme of this contest was to design a character that could be a possible crew member of Gargantia. About 900 entries were created by pixiv members! The entries were judged by director, Kazuya Murata, and the Gargantia animation staff." [1]

title: dlsite.com_15_year_anniversary_contest
body:
A mascot character contest held on Nico Nico Seiga for the 15 year anniversary of "DLsite.com":http://www.dlsite.com 

The theme was a "Home Security 'Girl'" (自宅警備 "娘"). This is a play on the slang term "Home Security Guard" (自宅警備員 [jitaku keibi'in], sometimes abbreviated as JK). The term means something like [[NEET]]. It's used for people that, instead of going to work or school, are at home all day. The joke is that they're not NEETs, they're home security guards. It's simply their job to stay home all day and "guard" it. See "here":http://bangin.wordpress.com/2008/10/07/%E8%87%AA%E5%AE%85%E8%AD%A6%E5%82%99%E5%93%A1jitaku-keibiin/ for more info on the term.
